@Mailaender: Under Ransomware protection I have Controlled folder access off, I tried temporarily disabling Real-time protection to no effect.

@pchote: I haven't made any manual changes to my install dir, but it is an upgrade of some older version - I think I uninstalled and reinstalled when the change from one EXE to multiple was made. I only have Windows Defender for real-time protection.

I have uninstalled and reinstalled, kept my old content folder - and it works fine (aaand there's a new version, which works fine too).

So it was a once-off installer bug?
